    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the stew has had 30 min in the oven, reboil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to<strong> </strong>an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
